info.title: Kyriosb Api
info.description:
Kyrios Tier B Api

**IMPORTANT MIGRATION NOTICE**
Kyrios is migrating from ECS to EKS by end of Q2 2025. Please update your integrations to use the new EKS URLs:

- US-East-1: https://dev-use1-apt-shared-main.plat.dev.aws.chewy.cloud/eks/app/kyrios-b
- US-East-2: https://dev-use2-apt-shared-main.plat.dev.aws.chewy.cloud/eks/app/kyrios-b

Current URLs will continue to function during the transition period.

weightType.description: Indicates pet weight classification (Underweight, Healthy Weight, Overweight)

sizeType.description: Indicates pet weight classification (Unknown, Extra Small, Small, Medium, Large, Extra Large, Giant)

fullGrownSizeType.description: Indicates pet size classification (Unknown, Extra Small, Small, Medium, Large, Extra Large, Giant)

lifestage.description: Indicates pet life stage classification (Senior, Adult, Puppy, Kitten)

statusReason.description: Indicates pet profile status reason classification

activityLevel.description: Indicates pet activity level (mellow, active, very-active)

items.description: Indicates pet fresh food exclusions (chicken, beef, lamb, turkey)

line1.description: Address line 1 containing the street address or PO Box

line2.description: Address line 2 containing the apartment or unit information for the address

stateCode.description: 2 letter code for state. Example MA for Massachussetts

countryCode.description: 2 letter country code. US for USA, CA for Canada

addressType.description: Type of address stored. This is a field provided by the service

subType.description: Indicates if special type of address

customerOverride.description: Indicator if the customer overrode the recommended address

type.description: Customer this request is being made on behalf of

CustomerResource.description: Customer this was done on behalf of

deliveryInstruction.description: Delivery instruction code (2-character code: FD, BD, SD, GA, ME, SG, AO, OT, NULL)

securityCode.description:
Security code for building or gate access (e.g., gate code, door code).
This field is masked in API responses unless the user has the
'address:security-code:read' scope for security purposes.

DeliveryInstructionResource.description: Structured delivery instruction details for shipping addresses

LastDeliveryResource.description: Last time this customer had a successful delivery to this address

LastShippedResource.description: Last time this customer had something shipped to them

entryPoint.description: Entrypoint application where this data came from. If you do not see your entrypoint, reach out to Kyrios team to add your entrypoint

PhoneResource.description: Phone number for communication from the delivery driver

type.description: Identifies what type the requestor is, giving context to the supplied requestorId. If you need a new type, reach out to Kyrios team

RequestorResource.description: Who is doing the action. Think Customer/Admin/System. If new type required, reach out to Kyrios team

label.description: Optional Label to describe what this address represents. Think Home or Family Member Address

userId.description: Customer this address is associated to

fullName.description: Name of who this shipping address is for

status.description: Determines the state of the address in the system

defaultAddress.description: This address is the default shipping address. Only one address linked to a customer can be marked default at a time

deliveryInstructions.description:
"Instructions for delivery driver. This currently isn't wired to OMS yet !!!Future use!!!")
 DEPRECATED: Legacy delivery instructions field. This field is deprecated and maintained for backward compatibility only.
 Please use the structured 'deliveryInstruction' object instead.

ShippingAttributesResource.description: Shipping-specific attributes and preferences for an address

status.description: This attribute returns the status determined by Kyrios for the given address after validation

engine.description: Chewy interacts with two verification engines for addresses. i) EXPERIAN , ii) FEDEXThis attribute returns the value of the engine against which the given address is validated

message.description: This attribute returns the problem/message corresponding to the status determined by Kyrios for the given address after validation
